\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5828348\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gmo1705664219831.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gmo1705664219831.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gmo1705664219831.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xrv1665702824708\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Define Toggle Symbols\n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Toggle symbols are language setups that define the default text for <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">askmess</span> answers, and the labels of the Character Attributes menu. They are not applicable to web or mobile applications.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"xrv1665702824708__context_l21_cxc_scc\">\n<p class=\"p\">To define your own toggle symbols:</p>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xrv1665702824708__li_d13757e1_d13758e1_d13759e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Editors</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\"> Toggle Symbols</span></span>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xrv1665702824708__li_d13760e1_d13761e1_d13762e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Select or create a message library to hold the language setup.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xrv1665702824708__li_d13763e1_d13764e1_d13765e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"xrv1665702824708__p_d26990e1_d26991e1_d26992e1\">Select the language for which you are defining toggle symbols.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xrv1665702824708__li_d13766e1_d13767e1_d13768e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"xrv1665702824708__p_d26993e1_d26994e1_d26995e1\">To define the texts for the Character Attributes\n               menu, enter the text you want to appear on the menu when that item is toggled on and\n               off <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Toggle On</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Toggle Off</span>\n               fields.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xrv1665702824708__li_d13769e1_d13770e1_d13771e1\">For example, in the USA language setup, the\n                     BOLD item has the text <code class=\"ph codeph\">no Bold</code> when it is toggled off and\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">Bold</code> when it is toggled on. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xrv1665702824708__li_d13772e1_d13773e1_d13774e1\">For the FONT action, the text you enter in\n                     the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Toggle On</span> field is used, for example,\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">Courier</code> or Helvetica. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xrv1665702824708__li_d13775e1_d13776e1_d13777e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"xrv1665702824708__p_d26996e1_d26997e1_d26998e1\">Specify the default replies for an\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">askmess</span> in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Default askmess Answers</span>\n               list box.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">You can define up to two sets of <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Positive</span>(toggle on) and\n                     <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Negative</span>(toggle off) replies that are recognized by the\n                  ProcScript <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">askmess</span> statement.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xrv1665702824708__p_d26999e1_d27000e1_d27001e1\">For example, if you are defining default\n                     <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">askmess</span> answers for a character mode application, you can\n                  capitalize the characters a user must enter. For character mode applications, you\n                  can also allow alternative values to be entered as affirmative and negative\n                  replies to an <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">askmess</span>. </p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mae1719381665957.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>askmess</a><p>Display a message and wait for the user's response.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5828348\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5828348\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define Toggle Symbols Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define Toggle Symbols Toggle symbols are language setups that define the default text for askmess answers, and the labels of the Character Attributes menu. They are not applicable to web or mobile applications. To define your own toggle symbols: Choose More Editors > Toggle Symbols . Select or create a message library to hold the language setup. Select the language for which you are defining toggle symbols. To define the texts for the Character Attributes menu, enter the text you want to appear on the menu when that item is toggled on and off Toggle On and Toggle Off fields. For example, in the USA language setup, the BOLD item has the text no Bold when it is toggled off and Bold when it is toggled on. For the FONT action, the text you enter in the Toggle On field is used, for example, Courier or Helvetica. Specify the default replies for an askmess in the Default askmess Answers list box. You can define up to two sets of Positive (toggle on) and Negative (toggle off) replies that are recognized by the ProcScript askmess statement. For example, if you are defining default askmess answers for a character mode application, you can capitalize the characters a user must enter. For character mode applications, you can also allow alternative values to be entered as affirmative and negative replies to an askmess . Related Links askmess Display a message and wait for the user's response. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}